					"alias": "/job/engineer/senior-engineering-manager/172808",
					"body": "<p><strong>Meet GetUpside:</strong></p><p><span >We created GetUpside to help communities thrive! Our retail technology uses the sophistication of online retail&mdash;profit measurement, attribution, and incrementality&mdash;to provide users with more value on their everyday purchases and brick and mortar businesses with new, profitable customers. We&rsquo;ve helped millions of users earn 2 to 3 times more cash back than any other product, and tens of thousands of brick and mortar businesses earn measurable profit. Billions of dollars in commerce runs through the GetUpside platform every year, and that value goes directly back to our local retailers, the consumers they serve, and towards important sustainability initiatives. Our mission, values, and commitment to inclusivity guide our team of more than 200 people worldwide, and the quality of our culture is reflected in the impact we&rsquo;ve had on communities nationwide.</span></p><p><strong>Meet the Multi Vertical team:</strong></p><ul><li><span >The Multi Vertical (MV) team is at the heart of our business, responsible for generating offers across all our business verticals and measuring the impact GetUpside users have generated for our merchants.</span></li><li><span >We work directly with our partners across the organization to enable new business opportunities and see them from ideation through to production.</span></li><li><span >We unlock new business opportunities and scales our business beyond the ones you&rsquo;ve come to know and love like Fuel and Groceries.</span></li><li><span >This team is also responsible for our Pricing, Optimization and Measurement platforms which supports our existing businesses.</span></li><li><span >Our goal is to support 10x growth across an increased range of businesses over the next 24 months.</span></li></ul><p><strong>About the job:</strong></p><p><span >The MV Engineering lead will work in close partnership with the Product teams as well as our internal business partners. Through these partnerships this leader will establish the engineering roadmap and will lead all aspects of its implementation to support our business needs. The leader will also be working across the engineering organization alongside the Machine Learning, Data, and Consumer Engineering teams to ensure that our solutions are aligned to company goals.</span></p><p><strong>What you'll do:</strong></p><ul><li><span >Lead the strategic and day-to-day engineering workload management of the team.</span></li><li><span >Use Agile methodologies to manage and deliver the teams&rsquo; OKRs.</span></li><li><span >Partner with our Product Managers to prioritize the work both tactically and strategically.</span></li><li><span >Build (in collaboration with the product management team) the OKRs, the roadmaps for the team, and drive the plans through sprints.</span></li><li><span >Shape the strategic direction of the organization.</span></li><li><span >Work with other engineering leads on the design of the future state of our platform.</span></li><li><span >Be responsible for the hiring, mentoring, career development, and organizational needs of your team.</span></li></ul><p><strong>What you need:</strong></p><ul><li><span >7-10 years experience building and leading high-impact teams.</span></li><li><span >5+ years of experience using cloud first technologies such as messaging, containers, relying on Identity management and other cloud-native tools (lambda, SNS, Redis, etc).</span></li><li><span >5-7 years of programming experience in either Python or Java.</span></li><li><span >Proven experience designing and implementing high performance platforms.</span></li><li><span >Skilled in collecting, analyzing and writing requirements.</span></li><li><span >Strong written and verbal communication skills and ability to work across multiple business and engineering organizations.</span></li></ul><p><strong>The fine print:</strong></p><ul><li><span >GetUpside employees are currently working from home during the COVID-19 pandemic. Afterwards our engineering teams are adopting a hybrid approach which can support full-time remote work while enabling in-person meetups as necessary.</span></li><li><strong>Notice to recruiters and placement agencies:</strong><span > This is an in-house search with a dedicated resource. Please do not submit resumes to any person or email address at GetUpside. GetUpside is not liable for, and will not pay, placement fees for candidates submitted by any party or agency other than its approved recruitment partners.</span></li></ul><p><span >At GetUpside, we believe that diversity drives innovation. Our differences are what makes us stronger. We&lsquo;re passionate about building a workplace that represents a variety of backgrounds, skills, and perspectives and do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status. Everyone is welcome here. Come join us!</span></p><b><span >#LI-NE1</span></b>",
