					"body": "<div><span >We believe manufacturing is important not only for what it makes, but for what it makes possible for the world. Manufacturers have an important job to do, and it&rsquo;s our job to provide them with the technology and expertise they need through the entire production process, from discovery and design to manufacturing and fulfillment.</span></div><div><br></div><div><span >We are currently looking for a Salesforce Expert with a passion for driving growth and productivity in sales organizations.</span></div><div><br></div><div><span >The ideal candidate has an analytical mind with the ability to act as a trusted adviser and business partner to Sales leaders, while working cross functionally with sales, marketing, and operations. The ideal candidate must be comfortable with ambiguity and adept at prescribing and prioritizing processes and tools to meet business problems.</span></div><p><b>About the Role:</b><ul><li>Supporting Fast Radius' sales leadership and operation teams to optimize the use of salesforce and ensure process adherence</li><li>Collaborating with the Sales Operations Director regarding SFDC improvement initiatives from data requirements to a successful roll-out.</li><li>Drive operational process and data flow logistics between systemsHelping to define the process, infrastructure and content related to training and user onboarding, ensuring excellent user engagement of sales enablement</li><li>Being a technical conduit and catalyst between the Sales Operations, marketing and Product on improvement initiatives, bugs, and technical fixes to maximize the operational excellence of the CRM</li><li>Acting as the SFDC Project manager on major improvement initiatives</li><li>Work with Enablement, Sales Systems & Operations, use the insights to surface potential issues, set priorities for addressing areas of improvement, and track progress against current goals</li><li>Provide day-to-day end user support and assist users with best practices to improve and increase their knowledge of Salesforce.com</li><li>Create and manage users, profiles, roles and permission sets in Salesforce</li><li>Assist in data import/export/updates, system customization</li><li>Build and maintain business automation processes with Flow Builder</li><li>Develop reports, dashboards, and processes to continuously monitor and identify insights from the user support requests we receive</li><li>Create training and user documentation, and maintain ongoing documentation processes as business needs evolve or features are added</li></ul></p><p><b>Minimum Requirements:</b><ul><li>5 years experience in a salesforce developer, revenue operations, Sales analyst, and/or salesforce administrator rol3</li><li>Salesforce Developer certification</li><li>Experience with Apex code</li><li>Proficient ability to build custom apps and objects, formula fields, workflows, custom views, Flows, Process Builders, and other content of intermediate complexity</li><li>Experience making bulk changes in salesforce using Data Import Wizard or DataLoader</li><li>Strong sense of urgency and ability to thrive in a dynamic, fast paced, results oriented environment</li><li>Strong analytical & problem solving skills</li><li>Driven and self motivated with a bias towards collaboration and a sense of urgency to deliver results</li></ul></p><p><b>Preferred Requirements:</b><ul><li>Experience configuring Marketo and Outreach</li><li>Entry level knowledge of SQL or SOQL</li><li>Proven ability to design and implement code to support complex processes</li><li>In-depth understanding of the capabilities and constraints of the platform</li><li>Strong understanding of Salesforce.com best practices and functionality</li><li>Strong data management abilities</li><li>A documented history of successfully driving projects to completion</li><li>A demonstrated ability to understand and articulate complex requirements</li></ul></p><p><div><b >Who we are: </b><b >&nbsp;</b><span >We believe manufacturing is important not only for what it makes but for what it makes possible for the world. Our first-of-its-kind Cloud Manufacturing Platform&trade; represents a new, more sustainable infrastructure to design, make, and move physical goods in the digital age. Working with companies across a variety of industries &ndash; from growing startups to Fortune 500 companies &ndash; Fast Radius helps customers with all stages of the manufacturing process from new product development to ongoing part production. </span><span >We recently became a publicly listed company</span><span > as the next step in scaling our vision for the future of design, manufacturing, and logistics.</span><span >&nbsp;</span><span >Every day you can expect to work in an inclusive environment that makes excellence possible, where great work and ideas matter more than seniority. We believe in experimenting fearlessly and learning from our failures&mdash;quickly. Our leaders have grown successful companies before, and they understand that businesses thrive when capable people have the freedom to solve problems without constraints.</span></div><div><br></div><div><b >What we offer: </b><span >We want you to come to work happy, healthy, and balanced so you can expect excellent benefits:&nbsp;</span></div><div><span >- Competitive compensation and bonus structure</span></div><div><span >- Comprehensive health care including dental and vision</span></div><div><span >- Generous vacation policy as well as a 401K plan </span></div><div><br></div><div><span >Fast Radius is proud to be an equal opportunity employer because diverse perspectives make for better products, better processes, and a better company. We encourage applicants from all backgrounds regardless of race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity/expression, national origin, ethnicity, age, disability, Veteran status, or other protected status.</span></div><div><br></div><div><span >Fast Radius currently is unable to sponsor or transfer visas.</span></div><div><br></div><div><span >We are currently able to hire residents in the following states: AL, AZ, CA, CO, CT, FL, GA, IL, IN, IA, KS, KY, MA, MD, MI, MN, NH, NJ, NY, NC, OH, OR, TN, TX, WA, WV, WI</span></div><p>",
