					"body": "<p><strong>What is Aclaimant?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aclaimant is a growth-stage SaaS company enabling the digital future of risk management and setting the standard for active risk management across the industry. Our comprehensive risk management platform empowers thousands of users to improve organizational behavior, create process efficiencies, and leverage the power of data and analytics to achieve better outcomes. We're adding top talent to continue this exciting growth; and invite candidates based and eligible to work in the U.S. to apply today!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why Join the Platform Team?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Work and learn with a highly collaborative team of the best engineers, developers, and quality assurance professionals that bring Aclaimants brightest ideas to life. Active Risk Management begins with an innovative approach to development that leverages both revolutionary and time-tested tools to create a world-class user experience and solve customers problems. Youll bring your superior software development skills and hone your expertise in designing risk management and safety solutions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What You'll Do:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li>Program and communicate with a highly engaged team that was founded on knowledge sharing with occasional pairing</li>\r\n\t<li>Maintain, own and drive production code standards and infrastructure across all domains</li>\r\n\t<li>Drive collaboration with our Product team to understand, ideate and implement new features</li>\r\n\t<li>Work across the organization with our Customer Success, Implementation, Data Services and other internal teams to better understand Customer needs driving us towards building solutions</li>\r\n\t<li>Help drive change in architecture, design, tooling, process, culture and beyond</li>\r\n\t<li>Grow your skills and help others to do the same acting as a project level mentor</li>\r\n\t<li>Participate in recruiting and interviewing as we grow our team making technically driven recommendations</li>\r\n\t<li>Make the occasional owl memes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What You'll Bring:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li>Embody the vision of teamwork and collaboration to accomplish shared goals</li>\r\n\t<li>Strong use of web markup, including HTML5, CSS3</li>\r\n\t<li>Broad understanding of CSS pre-processing platforms, such as LESS and SASS</li>\r\n\t<li>Demonstrate the ability to coach others in web technologies including JavaScript, React, Web Servers, HTTP and APIs</li>\r\n\t<li>Years of experience as a Front-End Engineer</li>\r\n\t<li>Nice to haves but not needed: Knowledge in Clojure, ClojureScript, relational databases, or SQL</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>You must be legally authorized to work in the U.S. as Aclaimant does not currently engage in immigration sponsorship</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Required Assessments</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li>After your initial interview with the team, you will be sent a small Code Challenge. This will not be a pass or fail, but more so an important step for you to show us how you solve a problem through code</li>\r\n\t<li>If moving forward after the Code Challenge, you will be invited to a live pairing session that mimics typical web development at Aclaimant where you will be able to use your own tools (editor/IDE), etc.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>We offer a competitive base salary&nbsp;that includes the employee's&nbsp;health benefits covered at 100%, 401(k) retirement plan with a match up to 4% of employee's contributions, flexible PTO, and remote work arrangements.</strong></p>\r\n",
